item.title: Power Measurement
item.description:
Power Measurement

This first post goes over measuring power of signals and computing signal to noise ratios. Differences between real-valued and complex valued signals are discussed. As well as

using Gadfly
using ColorSchemes
using Statistics
using Printf
using FFTW
set_default_plot_size(20cm, 15cm)
style(background_color=colorant"white");

function power(x::Vector{Float64})::Float64
    """
    power(x::Vector{Float64})::Float64

    Returns the average power (in dB) of the given sequence

    # Examples
    ```julia-repl
    julia> power([1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0])
    8.75
    ```
    """
    10 .* log10.(mean(abs.(x) .^ 2))
end

function power(x::Vector{ComplexF64})::Float64
    """
    power(x::Vector{Float64})::Float64

    Returns the average power (in dB) of the given sequence

    # Examples
    ```julia-repl
    julia> power([1.0+1im, 2.0+2im, 3.0+3im, 4.0+4im])
    11.76
    ```
    """
    10 .* log10.(mean(abs.(x) .^ 2))
end

power (generic function with 2 methods)

# Parameters for our signals
duration = 0.2           # Seconds
fs = 100e3               # Hz
f = 10e3                 # Hz
ϕ  = π / 4               # 
t = 1/fs:1/fs:duration   # Seconds
n = 100;                 #

Real Valued Signals

snr = 0  # dB
snr_linear = 10 .^ (snr ./ 10)
x = sqrt(2) * cos.(2π * f .* t .+ ϕ);
x_pwr = power(x)
x_pwr_linear = 10 .^ (x_pwr ./ 10)
noise = sqrt(x_pwr_linear ./ (snr_linear)) .* randn(Float64, size(x))

xₙ = x + noise
n_pwr = power(noise)
xₙ_pwr = power(xₙ)
snr = x_pwr .- n_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of x = %2.2f dB\n" x_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of noise = %2.2f dB\n" n_pwr
@printf "SNR = %2.2f dB\n" snr

Avg Power of x = 0.00 dB
Avg Power of noise = 0.02 dB
SNR = -0.02 dB

p_1 = plot(Guide.title("x (real valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude", orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))
p_2 = plot(Guide.title("xₙ (real valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude", orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))

push!(p_1, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(x[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(p_2, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(xₙ[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))

stack = vstack(p_1, p_2)

# PSD
fft_size = 4096
xf = (abs.(fft(xₙ[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs) 
nf = (abs.(fft(noise[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs) 
freqs = FFTW.fftfreq(length(xf), fs)
noise_floor = 10 * log10.(mean(nf))

freq_response = plot()
push!(freq_response, Guide.title("Frequency Response"), Guide.xlabel("Frequency [kHz]"), Guide.ylabel("Power Density [dB/Hz]", orientation=:vertical))
push!(freq_response, Coord.cartesian(xmin=-fs/(2 * 1e3), xmax=fs/(2*1e3), ymin=-100, ymax=-30))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=[-fs/(2 * 1e3), fs/(2*1e3)], y=[noise_floor, noise_floor], Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=freqs ./ 1e3, y=10 .* log10.(xf), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))

@printf "Measured Noise Power %2.1f dB/Hz\n" noise_floor
@printf "Theoretical Noise Power %2.1f dB/Hz\n" n_pwr - 10 * log10(fft_size) - 10 * log10(fs)
@printf "Peak power %2.1f dB/Hz" findmax(10 .* log10.(xf))[1]

Measured Noise Power -86.1 dB/Hz
Theoretical Noise Power -86.1 dB/Hz
Peak power -55.6 dB/Hz

Complex Valued Signals

snr = 0
snr_linear = 10 .^ (snr ./ 10)
x = ( im.* sin.(2π * f .* t .+ ϕ) + cos.(2π * f .* t .+ ϕ));
x_pwr = power(x)
x_pwr_linear = 10 .^ (x_pwr ./ 10)
noise = sqrt(x_pwr_linear ./ (snr_linear)) .* randn(ComplexF64, size(x))

xₙ = x + noise
n_pwr = power(noise)
xₙ_pwr = power(xₙ)
snr = x_pwr .- n_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of x = %2.2f dB\n" x_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of noise = %2.2f dB\n" n_pwr
@printf "SNR = %2.2f dB\n" snr

Avg Power of x = 0.00 dB
Avg Power of noise = 0.04 dB
SNR = -0.04 dB

p_1 = plot(Guide.title("x (complex valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude", orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))
p_2 = plot(Guide.title("xₙ (complex valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude",  orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))

push!(p_1, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(x[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))
push!(p_1, layer(x=t[1:n], y=imag(x[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(p_2, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(xₙ[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))
push!(p_2, layer(x=t[1:n], y=imag(xₙ[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))

stack = vstack(p_1, p_2)

# PSD
fft_size = 4096
xf = (abs.(fft(xₙ[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs)
nf = (abs.(fft(noise[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs)
freqs = FFTW.fftfreq(length(xf), fs)
noise_floor = 10 * log10.(mean(nf))

freq_response = plot()
push!(freq_response, Guide.title("Frequency Response"), Guide.xlabel("Frequency [kHz]"), Guide.ylabel("Power Density [dB/Hz]"))
push!(freq_response, Coord.cartesian(xmin=-fs/(2 * 1e3), xmax=fs/(2*1e3), ymin=-100, ymax=-30))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=[-fs/(2 * 1e3), fs/(2*1e3)], y=[noise_floor, noise_floor], Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=freqs ./ 1e3, y=10 .* log10.(xf), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))

@printf "Measured Noise Power %2.1f dB/Hz\n" noise_floor
@printf "Theoretical Noise Power %2.1f dB/Hz\n" n_pwr - 10 * log10(fft_size) - 10 * log10(fs)
@printf "Peak power %2.1f dB/Hz" findmax(10 .* log10.(xf))[1]

Measured Noise Power -86.1 dB/Hz
Theoretical Noise Power -86.1 dB/Hz
Peak power -52.1 dB/Hz

Note here that the real and complex values noise signals have the same power (-86 dB/Hz) but the power of the complex tone is 3 dB (factor of 2) higher. This is because there are two tones in the complex signal, the real part (in-phase) and the imaginary part (quadrature).

Signals With BW

function sinc(x)
   sin.(x) ./ (x); 
end

# Create sinc pulse and normalize to 0 dB
x₁ = sinc.(2π * f .* t .- 100π);
x₂ = x₁ ./ sqrt.(10 .^ (power(x₁)./10));        # note: var() returns the power of a signal (assuming 0 mean)
x = x₂
 
snr = 0
snr_linear = 10 .^ (snr ./ 10)
x_pwr = power(x)
x_pwr_linear = 10 .^ (x_pwr ./ 10)
noise = sqrt(x_pwr_linear ./ (snr_linear)) .* randn(Float64, size(x))

xₙ = x + noise
n_pwr = power(noise)
xₙ_pwr = power(xₙ)
snr = x_pwr .- n_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of x = %2.2f dB\n" x_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of noise = %2.2f dB\n" n_pwr
@printf "SNR = %2.2f dB\n" snr

Avg Power of x = 0.00 dB
Avg Power of noise = -0.01 dB
SNR = 0.01 dB

p_1 = plot(Guide.title("x (complex valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude", orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))
p_2 = plot(Guide.title("xₙ (complex valued signal)"), Guide.ylabel("Amplitude", orientation=:vertical), Guide.xlabel("Time [s]"))

n = 1000
push!(p_1, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(x[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))
push!(p_1, layer(x=t[1:n], y=imag(x[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(p_2, layer(x=t[1:n], y=real(xₙ[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))
push!(p_2, layer(x=t[1:n], y=imag(xₙ[1:n]), Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))

stack = vstack(p_1, p_2)

# PSD
fft_size = 4096
xf = (abs.(fft(x[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs)
nf = (abs.(fft(noise[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs)
xₙf = (abs.(fft(xₙ[1:fft_size])) ./ fft_size).^2 ./ (fs)
freqs = FFTW.fftfreq(length(xf), fs)
noise_floor = 10 * log10.(mean(nf))

Xf = fftshift(fft(x[1:fft_size]))  ./ fft_size
ind1 = Int64(ceil(fft_size/2 - f/(fs) * fft_size/2))
ind2 = Int64(floor(fft_size/2 + f/(fs) * fft_size/2))
signal_power = 10 * log10(mean(abs.(Xf[ind1:ind2]).^2))  - 10*log10(fs)

freq_response = plot()
push!(freq_response, Guide.title("Frequency Response"), Guide.xlabel("Frequency [kHz]"), Guide.ylabel("Power Density [dB/Hz]", orientation=:vertical))
push!(freq_response, Coord.cartesian(xmin=-fs/(2 * 1e3), xmax=fs/(2*1e3), ymin=-150, ymax=-30))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=[-fs/(2*1e3), fs/(2*1e3)], y=[noise_floor, noise_floor], Geom.line, color=[colorant"red"]))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=freqs ./ 1e3, y=10 .* log10.(xₙf), Geom.line, color=[colorant"green"]))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=freqs ./ 1e3, y=10 .* log10.(xf), Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))
push!(freq_response, layer(x=[-fs/(2*1e3), fs/(2*1e3)], y=[signal_power, signal_power], Geom.line, color=[colorant"blue"]))

x_pwr = power(x)
n_pwr = power(noise)
snr = x_pwr - n_pwr

@printf "Avg Power of x = %2.2f dB\n" x_pwr
@printf "Avg Power of noise = %2.2f dB\n" n_pwr
@printf "SNR = %2.2f dB\n" snr

Avg Power of x = 0.00 dB
Avg Power of noise = -0.01 dB
SNR = 0.01 dB
